  "definition": {
    "en": "Azosemide, when dried, contains not less than 99."
  },
  "appearance": {
    "en": "Azosemide occurs as a white to yellow-white crystalline powder. It is freely soluble in N,N-dimethylformamide, slightly soluble in methanol and in ethanol (99.5), and practically in-soluble in water. It dissolves in dilute sodium hydroxide TS. It is gradually colored to yellow by light. Each mL of 0.1 mol/L potassium hydroxide-ethanol VS ＝ 37.08 mg of C12H11ClN6O2S2"
  },
  "testSpecification": [
    {
      "@type": "AssaySpecification",
      "testName": {
        "en": "Assay"
      },
      "testType": "TestType-Assay",
      "testConditions": {
        "en": "Weigh accurately about 0.6 g of Azosemide, previ-ously dried, dissolve in 50 mL of N,N-dimethylformamide, and titrate <2.50> with 0.1 mol/L potassium hydroxide-ethanol VS until the color of the solution changes from yel-low to yellow-green (indicator: 10 drops of thymol blue-N,N-dimethylformamide TS). Perform a blank determina-tion in the same manner with a solution prepared by adding 15 mL of ethanol (95) to 50 mL of N,N-dimethylformamide, 12 11 6 2 2 and make any necessary correction. 2-Chloro-5-(1H-tetrazol-5-yl)-4-[(thien-2-ylmethyl)amino] benzenesulfonamide [27589-33-9] Azosemide, when dried, contains not less than 99.0z and not more than 101.0z of azosemide (C12H11ClN6O2S2). Description Azosemide occurs as a white to yellow-white crystalline powder. It is freely soluble in N,N-dimethylformamide, slightly soluble in methanol and in ethanol (99.5), and practically in-soluble in water. It dissolves in dilute sodium hydroxide TS. It is gradually colored to yellow by light. Each mL of 0.1 mol/L potassium hydroxide-ethanol VS ＝ 37.08 mg of C12H11ClN6O2S2"
      }
    }
  ],
  "storageConditions": {
    "en": "Containers—Tight containers. Storage—Light-resistant."
  }
}